    "body": "I had a feeling you were going to say that. I did not say put unbound requirements. From your example, it seems >=5.11,<=5.15 is a valid range, so why restrict further?\r\nWhen you restrict it, another projects called eth-brownie2, uses 5.12.0, and I can't have both.\r\n\r\nWhen you use brownie as an independent command line tool, your approach works. But when I use it as a library, where I import things, it imposes problems.\r\n\r\nI want to write tests that use our internal python libraries as well, so I need to install it as part of the same venv",
